https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/unZzdHAgW5hFz8kURgcovofvzsc.jpg Spanning his fifty-year dogsled racing career, ATTLA explores the life and persona of George Attla, from his childhood as a TB survivor in the Alaskan interior, to his rise as ten-time world champion and mythical state hero, to a village elder resolutely training his grandnephew to race his team one last time.
